- Your National Insurance credits are still protected (important if you're not working)
- Your children will still automatically get their National Insurance number at 16

The advantages of each approach:

1. Claiming and then paying back:
   - Provides you with the cash flow benefit during the year
   - But creates additional admin as your wife must complete a self-assessment tax return and pay back the amount in full

2. Opting out (waiving payment):
   - Less paperwork - no need for self-assessment if your wife doesn't otherwise need to do one
   - No need to budget for paying back the benefit
   - You still get all the non-payment benefits of being registered

Most families in your situation choose to opt out to avoid the administrative burden, but the choice depends on your personal circumstances and preferences.

